article.description: Mosley, Ross, Old Dominion beat George Mason 75-69
article.headline: Mosley, Ross, Old Dominion beat George Mason 75-69
article.linkText: Mosley, Ross, Old Dominion beat George Mason 75-69
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. -- Ambrose Mosley scored 10 of his career-high tying 21 points in the final 3 minutes to lead Old Dominion past George Mason 75-69 on Wednesday night. Mosley hit 5 of 10 from 3-point range and 6 of 6 free throws for Old Dominion (6-1), which made a season-high 11 3-pointers and converted 20 of 23 free throws. Richard Ross added 13 points and a career-high 14 rebounds -- 10 offensive. After Marquise Moore gave George Mason (2-5) a 62-60 lead with 3:13 to play, Mosley scored eight-straight points and Old Dominion led by six about 2 minutes later. Moore and ODU's Aaron Bacote exchanged a pair of free throws before Patrick Holloway hit a 3 to cut George Mason's deficit to 70-67 with 30 seconds left. Old Dominion made 5 of 6 free throws from there to seal it. Moore led George Mason with 22 points.
